# Cline Rules — Spec-Driven Platform V10
# Marine Guardian Enterprise
# Read automatically before every Cline task.

## CONTEXT LOAD ORDER (read ALL 9 before any task)

1. .cline/memory/lessons.md          ← READ FIRST — avoid repeating known errors
2. docs/PRODUCT.md                   ← single source of truth
3. inputs.yml                        ← derived spec (agent-owned)
4. inputs.schema.json                ← validation schema (agent-owned)
5. docs/CHANGELOG_AI.md              ← change history with agent attribution
6. docs/DECISIONS_LOG.md             ← locked architectural decisions
7. docs/IMPLEMENTATION_MAP.md        ← current implementation state
8. project.memory.md                 ← V10 rules + agent stack summary
9. .cline/memory/agent-log.md        ← what every agent has done

All 9 must be read before any implementation begins.
Never skip any of these — even for "small" changes.

---

## EXECUTION RULES

### Phase 4 — No stops
Run all 8 scaffold parts sequentially without stopping.
No "next" prompts. No confirmation between parts.
After Part 8 → automatically run Phase 5 validation.

### Phase 5 — Auto-validate
Run all 8 commands. Fix every failure. Never suppress TypeScript errors with `any`.
All 8 must be green before Phase 6.

### Phase 6 — Visual QA required (Rule 16)
After Docker services healthy → run browser QA against http://localhost:3000.
Minimum checks: app loads (no 5xx), login page renders, no console errors,
auth flow completes, GET /api/health returns 200.
If check fails: log to lessons.md, attempt one auto-fix, retry.
If still failing after retry: write handoff to .cline/handoffs/.

### Phase 7 — Feature Update order
1. Read all 9 context docs + lessons.md
2. SocratiCode search (Rule 17): codebase_search before opening any files
3. Confirm receipt (3–5 bullets on current status)
4. Rule 9 bidirectional check (REFUSE if violated)
5. Rule 11 removal check (list removals, ask confirmation)
6. Ask max 3 clarifying questions (only if genuinely needed)
7. Implement (surgical edits only — never full rewrites)
8. Update all governance docs (CHANGELOG_AI with attribution, IMPLEMENTATION_MAP, DECISIONS_LOG if new decision, agent-log, lessons if error resolved)
9. Visual QA (Rule 16)
10. Run codebase_update (Rule 17)
11. Deliver

---

## RULE 17 — SEARCH BEFORE READING (SocratiCode — V10)

MANDATORY search-first workflow for every Phase 7 and Phase 8:

```
1. codebase_search { query: "conceptual description of what you're looking for" }
   → returns ranked snippets from across the entire codebase
   → use for: "how is auth handled", "where is rate limiting", "find payment flow"

2. codebase_graph_query { filePath: "src/..." }
   → see imports + dependents BEFORE reading a file
   → use when you know the file but need to understand its impact

3. Read files ONLY after search results point to 1–3 specific files
   → never open files speculatively

4. For exact symbol/string lookups: use grep (faster for exact matches)
   → use codebase_search for natural-language / conceptual queries
   → use grep for exact identifiers, error strings, regex patterns
```

SocratiCode tools and when to use each:
- codebase_search         → conceptual queries, feature location, flow tracing
- codebase_graph_query    → dependency graph before reading a file
- codebase_graph_circular → when debugging unexpected behavior
- codebase_context_search → find schemas, API specs, infra configs by description
- codebase_status         → check if index is current (run after large refactors)
- codebase_update         → incremental re-index after every Phase 7 implementation
- codebase_index          → full index (first-time or after major scaffold)

Docker must be running for SocratiCode. If Docker is not running, log reminder
in agent-log.md: "SocratiCode index pending — start Docker and run codebase_index"

---

## ERROR RECOVERY RULES

- 3 auto-fix attempts per error before writing a handoff file
- Always read the full error output before attempting a fix
- Never suppress TypeScript errors with `@ts-ignore` or `any`
- After resolving an error: append to .cline/memory/lessons.md
- After 3 failed attempts: write handoff to .cline/handoffs/<timestamp>-<error-type>.md

### Handoff file format:
```markdown
# Handoff — <error type> — <timestamp>

## What I Was Doing
[phase + task description]

## Full Error Output
[complete error message]

## Fix Attempts
### Attempt 1
- What I tried: ...
- Result: still failing

### Attempt 2
- What I tried: ...
- Result: still failing

### Attempt 3
- What I tried: ...
- Result: still failing

## Root Cause (best assessment)
[diagnosis]

## What To Do Next
[recommended fix for human or other agent]
```

---

## GOVERNANCE RULES (enforced always)

- Rule 1: docs/PRODUCT.md is sole source of truth — never modify it
- Rule 9: Bidirectional governance — PRODUCT.md ↔ inputs.yml always in sync
- Rule 10: Never infer missing info — ask if any required section is blank
- Rule 11: Removal requires: list → confirm → delete + down-migration + update docs
- Rule 12: TypeScript strict everywhere — no any, no JS in src/
- Rule 15: Every CHANGELOG_AI.md entry must include Agent: CLINE
- Never modify .devcontainer after initial Phase 3 setup (Rule 8)

---

## AFTER EVERY TASK

Always append to:
- .cline/memory/agent-log.md (what was done)
- .cline/memory/lessons.md (if an error was resolved)
- docs/CHANGELOG_AI.md (Rule 15 format with Agent: CLINE)
- docs/IMPLEMENTATION_MAP.md (rewrite to reflect current state)
